//
// nettop - single-file Qt5 application with embedded libpcap capture,
// OpenStreetMap tile background, and nodes placed on the country/state/land
// centroid where each IP is inferred to be from.
//
// Features implemented in this amalgamated prototype:
// - Embedded libpcap capture thread (CaptureThread) that emits ConnectionEvent
// - GraphModel that stores nodes and edges; nodes get a country code via a
//   lightweight GeoResolver (reverse DNS TLD heuristic + small built-in centroid table).
// - TileManager (QNetworkAccessManager) that fetches OSM tiles and caches them on disk.
// - GLWidget that renders only the map tiles and nodes positioned by country centroid
//   (no force-directed topology). Nodes jitter slightly inside the country to avoid overlap.
// - UI: a minimal top bar with a Map Mode toggle (Map Mode is default on) and a small
//   recent events list on the right. Attribution for OpenStreetMap is shown.
//
// Notes and limitations:
// - This prototype avoids heavy external dependencies (no libmaxminddb required).
// - Country resolution is heuristic: it tries reverse DNS TLD, then falls back to a small
//   built-in centroid table for common countries. For production, integrate MaxMind DB.
// - Tile usage: default tile server is tile.openstreetmap.org. Respect OSM tile usage policy.
// - Live capture requires privileges (root or CAP_NET_RAW). Use with care.
//
// Build (example):
//   g++ -std=c++17 nettop.cpp -o nettop `pkg-config --cflags --libs Qt5Widgets Qt5Network Qt5Concurrent` -lpcap
//
// Run:
//   sudo ./nettop
//
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

